This paper discusses sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning methods, which is a common topic in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The development of a new method involves combining existing approaches, which falls under the sub-category of data fusion (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of lexical-based approaches, which is a common topic in the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper presents a free Web service, which falls under the sub-category of computer networks and communications (cs.CY).
